name: Observe -> Cables,
description: Look at the cables for any sign of damage, outcome="NOMINAL\n\nAll inspected cables (PSU Output, Control Input/Output, and Load Input, both positive and negative) were visually observed and no observable internal faults or signs of rupture/damage were detected. All cables are reported as connected at both ends. No anomalous behavior or indication of the problem ['CablesRuptured'] was found based on the inspection results. Proceeding to next diagnostic steps is recommended if cable issues are still suspected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Battery,
description: Look at the battery for signs of improper installation or defect, outcome="NOMINAL\n\nBased on the visual inspection of the battery, there were no observable signs of improper installation or defect. The battery appears intact and free from internal faults. No anomalous behavior suggesting the problem 'BatteryDamaged' was detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Battery,
description: Use a voltimeter to test the battery energy content, outcome="NOMINAL\n\nBased on the measurement taken with the voltmeter, the voltage at the positive terminal of the battery is 12.0 V, while the negative terminal reads 0.0 V (which is expected, assuming it is referenced to ground). This voltage level is typical for a healthy, charged 12 V battery, indicating that the battery is not depleted at the time of the test. No anomalous behavior suggesting 'BatteryDepleted' was found in this measurement.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switch,
description: With a multimiter, close the switch and test for continuity between the switch ports (there should be continuity), then open the switch and test for continuity again (there should be no continuity)., outcome='NOMINAL\n\nFeedback:\nThe test procedure for the switch was executed correctly. When the switch was closed, there was continuity (measured resistance ~0.01 Ω, indicating a short), and when the switch was opened, there was no continuity (measured resistance very high, indicating open circuit). These results are as expected for a functional switch. No anomalous behavior or signs of a SwitchInternalFault were detected during this test. The switch appears to be operating normally.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\n  • Control Switch: OPEN', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('open_switch', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Replace -> 3CubesSystem,
description: Replace an indicator, may be any of the indicators present in the system, outcome="NOMINAL\n\nAll three indicator replacements (PSU Status LED, Inverted Cables Indicator, Internal Indicator Lamp) were executed successfully, with step outcome messages confirming each indicator was replaced and parameters restored to nominal. There is no evidence of anomalous behavior suggestive of the problem ['NoIndication']. \n\nIf the original issue was a lack of indication, these steps should now have resolved it. Please verify actual indicator operation during system power-up or use to confirm restoration.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\n  • Control Switch: OPEN", precise_action_cost=360.0, cost_breakdown=[('replace_component', 120.0), ('replace_component', 120.0), ('replace_component', 120.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> InternalIndicatorLamp,
description: Look through the pinhole in the load module to see if the small lamp turns on when the switch is operated and power is supplied to the circuit., outcome='NOMINAL\n\nThe internal indicator lamp is **not lit** when the switch is operated and power is supplied. This suggests there is **no voltage detected** across the branch, and the main load is likely not carrying current either. Therefore, no anomalous behavior was observed in the indicator lamp, and the problem is not necessarily with the main load’s installation or filament. Further investigation upstream (e.g., power supply, switch, wiring) is needed, as both the main load and the indicator lamp are showing consistent results.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\n  • Control Switch: OPEN', precise_action_cost=15.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
